review_blob: Tasted on tap at the brewery during the tour.  Very nice example of a maerzen/oktoberfest style. light amber appearance with a pure white head.  Up front malty with a little pecan nuttiness that is nicely balance out with some noble hop bitterness.  I enjoyed sufficiently enough to buy a case!  Prosit!
overall impression is good with big malt flavor.  finish is somewhat dry and nicely balances the big malty taste.
The gold standard for alt beers.  Malty with a nice hop background.  My favorite beerstyle and my favorite beer from this style.
